
iptables - standard firewall software, use set of rules to filter the network traffic

iptables can be configured via rules applied on chains:
Input chain - handles incomming traffic
Output chain - handles outgoing traffic
Forward chain - handles routing traffic

#----------------COMMON IPTABLES RULES-------------
sudo iptables -L	#list current iptables rules
sudo iptables -A INPUT -p tcp --dport 4321 -j ACCEPT	#allows incomming tcp traffic from port 4321
sudo iptables -A INPUT -j DROP				#blocks all incomming traffic
sudo iptables-save
sudo iptables-save > iptables-save
sudo iptables-save > iptables-restore

#man iptables - full iptables manual
